24// This small structure encapsulates binding sampler uniforms to active GL textures.
25struct SamplerBinding
26{
27 SamplerBinding(TextureType textureTypeIn, SamplerFormat formatIn, size_t elementCount);
28 SamplerBinding(const SamplerBinding &other);
29 ~SamplerBinding();
30
31 // Necessary for retrieving active textures from the GL state.
32 TextureType textureType;
33
34 SamplerFormat format;
35
36 // List of all textures bound to this sampler, of type textureType.
37 // Cropped by the amount of unused elements reported by the driver.
38 std::vector<GLuint> boundTextureUnits;
39};
40
41struct ImageBinding
42{
43 ImageBinding(size_t count);
44 ImageBinding(GLuint imageUnit, size_t count);
45 ImageBinding(const ImageBinding &other);
46 ~ImageBinding();
47
48 // List of all textures bound.
49 // Cropped by the amount of unused elements reported by the driver.
50 std::vector<GLuint> boundImageUnits;
51};
52
53// A varying with transform feedback enabled. If it's an array, either the whole array or one of its
54// elements specified by 'arrayIndex' can set to be enabled.
55struct TransformFeedbackVarying : public sh::ShaderVariable
56{
57 TransformFeedbackVarying(const sh::ShaderVariable &varyingIn, GLuint arrayIndexIn)
58 : sh::ShaderVariable(varyingIn), arrayIndex(arrayIndexIn)
59 {
60 ASSERT(!isArrayOfArrays());
61 }
62
63 TransformFeedbackVarying(const sh::ShaderVariable &field, const sh::ShaderVariable &parent)
64 : arrayIndex(GL_INVALID_INDEX)
65 {
66 sh::ShaderVariable *thisVar = this;
67 *thisVar = field;
68 interpolation = parent.interpolation;
69 isInvariant = parent.isInvariant;
70 name = parent.name + "." + name;
71 mappedName = parent.mappedName + "." + mappedName;
72 }
73
74 std::string nameWithArrayIndex() const
75 {
76 std::stringstream fullNameStr;
77 fullNameStr << name;
78 if (arrayIndex != GL_INVALID_INDEX)
79 {
80 fullNameStr << "[" << arrayIndex << "]";
81 }
82 return fullNameStr.str();
83 }
84 GLsizei size() const
85 {
86 return (isArray() && arrayIndex == GL_INVALID_INDEX ? getOutermostArraySize() : 1);
87 }
88
89 GLuint arrayIndex;
90};

95class ProgramExecutable final : public angle::Subject
96{
97 public:
98 ProgramExecutable();
99 ProgramExecutable(const ProgramExecutable &other);
100 ~ProgramExecutable() override;
101
102 void reset();
103
104 void save(gl::BinaryOutputStream *stream) const;
105 void load(gl::BinaryInputStream *stream);
106
107 int getInfoLogLength() const;
108 InfoLog &getInfoLog() { return mInfoLog; }
109 void getInfoLog(GLsizei bufSize, GLsizei *length, char *infoLog) const;
110 std::string getInfoLogString() const;
111 void resetInfoLog() { mInfoLog.reset(); }
112
113 void resetLinkedShaderStages()
114 {
115 mLinkedComputeShaderStages.reset();
116 mLinkedGraphicsShaderStages.reset();
117 }
118 const ShaderBitSet &getLinkedShaderStages() const
119 {
120 return isCompute() ? mLinkedComputeShaderStages : mLinkedGraphicsShaderStages;
121 }
122 void setLinkedShaderStages(ShaderType shaderType)
123 {
124 if (shaderType == ShaderType::Compute)
125 {
126 mLinkedComputeShaderStages.set(ShaderType::Compute);
127 }
128 else
129 {
130 mLinkedGraphicsShaderStages.set(shaderType);
131 }
132
133 updateCanDrawWith();
134 }
135 bool hasLinkedShaderStage(ShaderType shaderType) const
136 {
137 ASSERT(shaderType != ShaderType::InvalidEnum);
138 return (shaderType == ShaderType::Compute) ? mLinkedComputeShaderStages[shaderType]
139 : mLinkedGraphicsShaderStages[shaderType];
140 }
141 size_t getLinkedShaderStageCount() const
142 {
143 return isCompute() ? mLinkedComputeShaderStages.count()
144 : mLinkedGraphicsShaderStages.count();
145 }
146
147 // A PPO can have both graphics and compute programs attached, so
148 // we don't know if the PPO is a 'graphics' or 'compute' PPO until the
149 // actual draw/dispatch call.
150 bool isCompute() const { return mIsCompute; }
151 void setIsCompute(bool isCompute) { mIsCompute = isCompute; }
152
153 const AttributesMask &getActiveAttribLocationsMask() const
154 {
155 return mActiveAttribLocationsMask;
156 }
157 bool isAttribLocationActive(size_t attribLocation) const;
158 const AttributesMask &getNonBuiltinAttribLocationsMask() const { return mAttributesMask; }
159 unsigned int getMaxActiveAttribLocation() const { return mMaxActiveAttribLocation; }
160 const ComponentTypeMask &getAttributesTypeMask() const { return mAttributesTypeMask; }
161 AttributesMask getAttributesMask() const;
162
163 const ActiveTextureMask &getActiveSamplersMask() const { return mActiveSamplersMask; }
164 void setActiveTextureMask(ActiveTextureMask mask) { mActiveSamplersMask = mask; }
165 SamplerFormat getSamplerFormatForTextureUnitIndex(size_t textureUnitIndex) const
166 {
167 return mActiveSamplerFormats[textureUnitIndex];
168 }
169 const ShaderBitSet getSamplerShaderBitsForTextureUnitIndex(size_t textureUnitIndex) const
170 {
171 return mActiveSamplerShaderBits[textureUnitIndex];
172 }
173 const ActiveTextureMask &getActiveImagesMask() const { return mActiveImagesMask; }
174 void setActiveImagesMask(ActiveTextureMask mask) { mActiveImagesMask = mask; }
175 const ActiveTextureArray<ShaderBitSet> &getActiveImageShaderBits() const
176 {
177 return mActiveImageShaderBits;
178 }
179
180 const ActiveTextureArray<TextureType> &getActiveSamplerTypes() const
181 {
182 return mActiveSamplerTypes;
183 }
184
185 void updateActiveSamplers(const ProgramState &programState);
186
187 bool hasDefaultUniforms() const;
188 bool hasTextures() const;
189 bool hasUniformBuffers() const;
190 bool hasStorageBuffers() const;
191 bool hasGraphicsStorageBuffers() const;
192 bool hasComputeStorageBuffers() const;
193 bool hasAtomicCounterBuffers() const;
194 bool hasImages() const;
195 bool hasGraphicsImages() const;
196 bool hasComputeImages() const;
197 bool hasTransformFeedbackOutput() const
198 {
199 return !getLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings().empty();
200 }
201
202 // Count the number of uniform and storage buffer declarations, counting arrays as one.
203 size_t getTransformFeedbackBufferCount() const { return mTransformFeedbackStrides.size(); }
204
205 bool linkValidateGlobalNames(InfoLog &infoLog,
206 const ShaderMap<const ProgramState *> &programStates) const;
207
208 void updateCanDrawWith();
209 bool hasVertexAndFragmentShader() const { return mCanDrawWith; }
210
211 const std::vector<sh::ShaderVariable> &getProgramInputs() const { return mProgramInputs; }
212 const std::vector<sh::ShaderVariable> &getOutputVariables() const { return mOutputVariables; }
213 const std::vector<VariableLocation> &getOutputLocations() const { return mOutputLocations; }
214 const std::vector<LinkedUniform> &getUniforms() const { return mUniforms; }
215 const std::vector<InterfaceBlock> &getUniformBlocks() const { return mUniformBlocks; }
216 const std::vector<SamplerBinding> &getSamplerBindings() const { return mSamplerBindings; }
217 const std::vector<ImageBinding> &getImageBindings() const
218 {
219 return isCompute() ? mComputeImageBindings : mGraphicsImageBindings;
220 }
221 std::vector<ImageBinding> *getImageBindings()
222 {
223 return isCompute() ? &mComputeImageBindings : &mGraphicsImageBindings;
224 }
225 const RangeUI &getDefaultUniformRange() const { return mDefaultUniformRange; }
226 const RangeUI &getSamplerUniformRange() const { return mSamplerUniformRange; }
227 const RangeUI &getImageUniformRange() const { return mImageUniformRange; }
228 const std::vector<TransformFeedbackVarying> &getLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings() const
229 {
230 return mLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings;
231 }
232 void setLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings(
233 const std::vector<TransformFeedbackVarying> _mLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings)
234 {
235 mLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings = _mLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings;
236 }
237 GLint getTransformFeedbackBufferMode() const { return mTransformFeedbackBufferMode; }
238 GLuint getUniformBlockBinding(GLuint uniformBlockIndex) const
239 {
240 ASSERT(uniformBlockIndex < mUniformBlocks.size());
241 return mUniformBlocks[uniformBlockIndex].binding;
242 }
243 GLuint getShaderStorageBlockBinding(GLuint blockIndex) const
244 {
245 ASSERT((isCompute() && (blockIndex < mComputeShaderStorageBlocks.size())) ||
246 (!isCompute() && (blockIndex < mGraphicsShaderStorageBlocks.size())));
247 return isCompute() ? mComputeShaderStorageBlocks[blockIndex].binding
248 : mGraphicsShaderStorageBlocks[blockIndex].binding;
249 }
250 const std::vector<GLsizei> &getTransformFeedbackStrides() const
251 {
252 return mTransformFeedbackStrides;
253 }
254 const std::vector<AtomicCounterBuffer> &getAtomicCounterBuffers() const
255 {
256 return mAtomicCounterBuffers;
257 }
258 const std::vector<InterfaceBlock> &getShaderStorageBlocks() const
259 {
260 return isCompute() ? mComputeShaderStorageBlocks : mGraphicsShaderStorageBlocks;
261 }
262 const LinkedUniform &getUniformByIndex(GLuint index) const
263 {
264 ASSERT(index < static_cast<size_t>(mUniforms.size()));
265 return mUniforms[index];
266 }
267
268 ANGLE_INLINE GLuint getActiveUniformBlockCount() const
269 {
270 return static_cast<GLuint>(mUniformBlocks.size());
271 }
272
273 ANGLE_INLINE GLuint getActiveAtomicCounterBufferCount() const
274 {
275 return static_cast<GLuint>(mAtomicCounterBuffers.size());
276 }
277
278 ANGLE_INLINE GLuint getActiveShaderStorageBlockCount() const
279 {
280 size_t shaderStorageBlocksSize =
281 isCompute() ? mComputeShaderStorageBlocks.size() : mGraphicsShaderStorageBlocks.size();
282 return static_cast<GLuint>(shaderStorageBlocksSize);
283 }
284
285 GLuint getUniformIndexFromImageIndex(GLuint imageIndex) const;
286
287 gl::ProgramLinkedResources &getResources() const
288 {
289 ASSERT(mResources);
290 return *mResources;
291 }
292
293 void saveLinkedStateInfo(const ProgramState &state);
294 std::vector<sh::ShaderVariable> getLinkedOutputVaryings(ShaderType shaderType)
295 {
296 return mLinkedOutputVaryings[shaderType];
297 }
298 std::vector<sh::ShaderVariable> getLinkedInputVaryings(ShaderType shaderType)
299 {
300 return mLinkedInputVaryings[shaderType];
301 }
302 int getLinkedShaderVersion(ShaderType shaderType) { return mLinkedShaderVersions[shaderType]; }
303
304 private:
305 // TODO(timvp): http://anglebug.com/3570: Investigate removing these friend

309 friend class ProgramState;

311 void updateActiveImages(const ProgramExecutable &executable);
312
313 // Scans the sampler bindings for type conflicts with sampler 'textureUnitIndex'.
314 void setSamplerUniformTextureTypeAndFormat(size_t textureUnitIndex,
315 std::vector<SamplerBinding> &samplerBindings);
316
317 InfoLog mInfoLog;
318
319 ShaderBitSet mLinkedGraphicsShaderStages;
320 ShaderBitSet mLinkedComputeShaderStages;
321
322 angle::BitSet<MAX_VERTEX_ATTRIBS> mActiveAttribLocationsMask;
323 unsigned int mMaxActiveAttribLocation;
324 ComponentTypeMask mAttributesTypeMask;
325 // mAttributesMask is identical to mActiveAttribLocationsMask with built-in attributes removed.
326 AttributesMask mAttributesMask;
327
328 // Cached mask of active samplers and sampler types.
329 ActiveTextureMask mActiveSamplersMask;
330 ActiveTextureArray<uint32_t> mActiveSamplerRefCounts;
331 ActiveTextureArray<TextureType> mActiveSamplerTypes;
332 ActiveTextureArray<SamplerFormat> mActiveSamplerFormats;
333 ActiveTextureArray<ShaderBitSet> mActiveSamplerShaderBits;
334
335 // Cached mask of active images.
336 ActiveTextureMask mActiveImagesMask;
337 ActiveTextureArray<ShaderBitSet> mActiveImageShaderBits;
338
339 bool mCanDrawWith;
340
341 // Names and mapped names of output variables that are arrays include [0] in the end, similarly
342 // to uniforms.
343 std::vector<sh::ShaderVariable> mOutputVariables;
344 std::vector<VariableLocation> mOutputLocations;
345 // Vertex attributes, Fragment input varyings, etc.
346 std::vector<sh::ShaderVariable> mProgramInputs;
347 std::vector<TransformFeedbackVarying> mLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings;
348 // The size of the data written to each transform feedback buffer per vertex.
349 std::vector<GLsizei> mTransformFeedbackStrides;
350 GLenum mTransformFeedbackBufferMode;
351 // Uniforms are sorted in order:
352 // 1. Non-opaque uniforms
353 // 2. Sampler uniforms
354 // 3. Image uniforms
355 // 4. Atomic counter uniforms
356 // 5. Uniform block uniforms
357 // This makes opaque uniform validation easier, since we don't need a separate list.
358 // For generating the entries and naming them we follow the spec: GLES 3.1 November 2016 section
359 // 7.3.1.1 Naming Active Resources. There's a separate entry for each struct member and each
360 // inner array of an array of arrays. Names and mapped names of uniforms that are arrays include
361 // [0] in the end. This makes implementation of queries simpler.
362 std::vector<LinkedUniform> mUniforms;
363 RangeUI mDefaultUniformRange;
364 RangeUI mSamplerUniformRange;
365 std::vector<InterfaceBlock> mUniformBlocks;
366 std::vector<AtomicCounterBuffer> mAtomicCounterBuffers;
367 RangeUI mImageUniformRange;
368 std::vector<InterfaceBlock> mComputeShaderStorageBlocks;
369 std::vector<InterfaceBlock> mGraphicsShaderStorageBlocks;
370
371 // An array of the samplers that are used by the program
372 std::vector<SamplerBinding> mSamplerBindings;
373
374 // An array of the images that are used by the program
375 std::vector<ImageBinding> mComputeImageBindings;
376 std::vector<ImageBinding> mGraphicsImageBindings;
377
378 // TODO: http://anglebug.com/3570: Remove mPipelineHas*UniformBuffers once PPO's have valid data
379 // in mUniformBlocks
380 bool mPipelineHasGraphicsUniformBuffers;
381 bool mPipelineHasComputeUniformBuffers;
382 bool mPipelineHasGraphicsStorageBuffers;
383 bool mPipelineHasComputeStorageBuffers;
384 bool mPipelineHasGraphicsAtomicCounterBuffers;
385 bool mPipelineHasComputeAtomicCounterBuffers;
386 bool mPipelineHasGraphicsDefaultUniforms;
387 bool mPipelineHasComputeDefaultUniforms;
388 bool mPipelineHasGraphicsTextures;
389 bool mPipelineHasComputeTextures;
390 bool mPipelineHasGraphicsImages;
391 bool mPipelineHasComputeImages;
392
393 bool mIsCompute;
394
395 ShaderMap<std::vector<sh::ShaderVariable>> mLinkedOutputVaryings;
396 ShaderMap<std::vector<sh::ShaderVariable>> mLinkedInputVaryings;
397 ShaderMap<int> mLinkedShaderVersions;
398 // TODO: http://anglebug.com/4514: Remove
399 std::unique_ptr<gl::ProgramLinkedResources> mResources;
400};
